From Wikipedia: &quot;Alone Against Tomorrow: Stories of Alienation in Speculative Fiction is a collection of short stories by author Harlan Ellison. Published in the United States in 1971, as a ten-year retrospective of Ellison's short stories, it includes some of his most famous work ... All of the stories in this collection center around isolation and alienation, and were selected from previous short story collections to fit this theme.&quot;

